      "author": "greg_elevate (Gregory Thomson)",
      "cookedHtml": "<p>Hey <a class=\"mention\" href=\"/u/costavia\">@costavia</a>! This doesn’t work retroactively (meaning you’ll probably have to enter historical values manually), but this automation works to count the number of updates as they come in:</p>\n<p></p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/original/2X/3/3dad689d5f56e9b08e02662dd61754c937f1fdd6.png\" title=\"update number\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"><img src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/optimized/2X/3/3dad689d5f56e9b08e02662dd61754c937f1fdd6_2_690x332.png\" alt=\"update number\" width=\"690\" height=\"332\" /><div class=\"meta\">\n<span class=\"filename\">update number</span><span class=\"informations\">1837×886 15.3 KB</span>\n</div></a></div><p></p>\n<p>Let me know if you have any questions! You can reach out here or at <a href=\"mailto:greg@elevateops.io\">greg@elevateops.io</a>.</p>"
